In [66]:
# INTERPRETING DATASETS
# 
# HOURLY PRICE:
# Delivery Date - Calendar date when the price shown applied.
# Hour Ending - The hour for which the price shown applied.
# Repeated Hour Flag - Tells whether or not this hour was repeated due to daylight savings.
# REGDN - Regulation Down. Price for backup that can quickly reduce power to keep the grid stable.
# REGUP - Regulation Up. Price for backup that can quickly increase power to keep the grid stable.
# RRS - Responsive Reserve. Price for fast emergency reserves ready if something suddenly fails.
# NSPINN - on-Spinning Reserve. Price for backup generators that are off, but can start up quickly if needed.
# ECRS - Contingency Reserve. Price for slower emergency reserves used during bigger problems on the grid. 
#
#
# HOURLY LOAD:
# "COAST":"Hou_Galv",
# "EAST":"East",
# "FWEST":"FW_West_Central",
# "NORTH":"North",
# "NCENT":"North_Central",
# "SOUTH":"South",
# "SCENT":"South_Central",
# "WEST":"West",
# "ERCOT":"Total_System_Load"
#

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

df_all = pd.concat([hourlyload24.copy(), hourlyload25.copy()], ignore_index=True)

df_all["Hour_of_Day"] = (
    df_all["Hour Ending"]
    .astype(str)
    .str.extract(r"(\d{1,2}):")[0]
    .replace("24", "0")
    .astype(int)
    + 1
)

zone_columns = [c for c in df_all.columns if c not in ["Hour Ending"]]
df_all[zone_columns] = df_all[zone_columns].apply(pd.to_numeric, errors="coerce")

df_all["Avg_Zone_Load"] = df_all[zone_columns].mean(axis=1)

df_all_daily_profile = df_all.groupby("Hour_of_Day")["Avg_Zone_Load"].mean().reset_index()

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.plot(
    df_all_daily_profile["Hour_of_Day"],
    df_all_daily_profile["Avg_Zone_Load"],
    marker="o",
    linestyle="-",
    color="green",
    linewidth=2
)

plt.title("20242025 Average Hourly Power Load")
plt.xlabel("Hour of Day (1 = 1:00 AM, 24 = 12:00 AM Next Day)")
plt.ylabel("Average Load (MW)")
plt.xticks(df_all_daily_profile["Hour_of_Day"][::2])
plt.grid(True, linestyle="--", alpha=0.6)
plt.tight_layout()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

df_load = pd.concat([hourlyload24.copy(), hourlyload25.copy()], ignore_index=True)
df_load["Hour_of_Day"] = (
    df_load["Hour Ending"]
    .astype(str)
    .str.extract(r"(\d{1,2}):")[0]
    .replace("24", "0")
    .astype(int)
    + 1
)
zone_columns = [c for c in df_load.columns if c not in ["Hour Ending"]]
df_load[zone_columns] = df_load[zone_columns].apply(pd.to_numeric, errors="coerce")
df_load["Avg_Zone_Load"] = df_load[zone_columns].mean(axis=1)
df_load_hourly = df_load.groupby("Hour_of_Day")["Avg_Zone_Load"].mean().reset_index()

df_price = pd.concat([hourlyprice24.copy(), hourlyprice25.copy()], ignore_index=True)
df_price["Hour_of_Day"] = (
    df_price["Hour Ending"]
    .astype(str)
    .str.extract(r"(\d{1,2}):")[0]
    .replace("24", "0")
    .astype(int)
    + 1
)
price_col = "Settlement Point Price"
df_price[price_col] = pd.to_numeric(df_price[price_col], errors="coerce")

if "Settlement Point Type" in df_price.columns:
    df_price = df_price[df_price["Settlement Point Type"] == "LZ"]

df_price_hourly = df_price.groupby("Hour_of_Day")[price_col].median().reset_index()

merged = pd.merge(df_load_hourly, df_price_hourly, on="Hour_of_Day")

fig, ax1 = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))

ax1.plot(
    merged["Hour_of_Day"],
    merged["Avg_Zone_Load"],
    marker="o",
    linestyle="-",
    color="green",
    linewidth=2,

)

ax1.tick_params(axis="y", labelcolor="green")

ax2 = ax1.twinx()
ax2.plot(
    merged["Hour_of_Day"],
    merged[price_col],
    marker="o",
    linestyle="-",
    color="red",
    linewidth=2,
    label="Median DAM Price ($/MWh)"
)
ax2.set_ylabel("Median DAM Price ($/MWh)", color="red")

xticks = merged["Hour_of_Day"][::2]

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

dfp_all = pd.concat([hourlyprice24.copy(), hourlyprice25.copy()], ignore_index=True)

dfp_all["Hour_of_Day"] = (
    dfp_all["Hour Ending"]
    .astype(str)
    .str.extract(r"(\d{1,2}):")[0]
    .replace("24", "0")
    .astype(int)
    + 1
)

price_col = "Settlement Point Price"
sp_col = "Settlement Point"
sptype_col = "Settlement Point Type" if "Settlement Point Type" in dfp_all.columns else None

if sptype_col:
    dfp_all = dfp_all[dfp_all[sptype_col] == "LZ"]

dfp_all = dfp_all[dfp_all[sp_col] == "LZ_WEST"]
dfp_all[price_col] = pd.to_numeric(dfp_all[price_col], errors="coerce")

q_low = dfp_all[price_col].quantile(0.01)
q_high = dfp_all[price_col].quantile(0.99)
dfp_all[price_col] = dfp_all[price_col].clip(lower=q_low, upper=q_high)

dfp_hourly = dfp_all.groupby("Hour_of_Day")[price_col].mean().reset_index()
dfp_hourly["Price_smooth"] = dfp_hourly[price_col].rolling(window=3, center=True, min_periods=1).mean()

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.plot(
    dfp_hourly["Hour_of_Day"],
    dfp_hourly["Price_smooth"],
    marker="o",
    linestyle="-",
    color="red",
    linewidth=2
)

plt.title("20242025 Smoothed Average DAM Price by Hour (LZ_WEST)")
plt.xlabel("Hour of Day (1 = 1:00 AM, 24 = 12:00 AM Next Day)")
plt.ylabel("Average DAM Price ($/MWh)")
plt.xticks(dfp_hourly["Hour_of_Day"][::2])
plt.grid(True, linestyle="--", alpha=0.6)

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

dfp_all = pd.concat([hourlyprice24.copy(), hourlyprice25.copy()], ignore_index=True)

dfp_all["Hour_of_Day"] = (
    dfp_all["Hour Ending"]
    .astype(str)
    .str.extract(r"(\d{1,2}):")[0]
    .replace("24", "0")
    .astype(int)
    + 1
)

price_col = "Settlement Point Price"
sp_col = "Settlement Point"
sptype_col = "Settlement Point Type" if "Settlement Point Type" in dfp_all.columns else None

if sptype_col:
    dfp_all = dfp_all[dfp_all[sptype_col] == "LZ"]

dfp_all = dfp_all[dfp_all[sp_col] == "LZ_WEST"]
dfp_all[price_col] = pd.to_numeric(dfp_all[price_col], errors="coerce")

q_low = dfp_all[price_col].quantile(0.01)
q_high = dfp_all[price_col].quantile(0.99)
dfp_all[price_col] = dfp_all[price_col].clip(lower=q_low, upper=q_high)

dfp_hourly = dfp_all.groupby("Hour_of_Day")[price_col].mean().reset_index()
dfp_hourly["Price_smooth"] = dfp_hourly[price_col].rolling(window=3, center=True, min_periods=1).mean()

theta = 2 * np.pi * (dfp_hourly["Hour_of_Day"] - 1) / 24

p = dfp_hourly["Price_smooth"].values
p_norm = (p - p.min()) / (p.max() - p.min() + 1e-9)

r_base = 1.0
r_spike = r_base + 0.7 * p_norm

fig = plt.figure(figsize=(8, 8))
ax = fig.add_subplot(111, projection="polar")

ax.set_theta_direction(-1)
ax.set_theta_offset(np.pi / 2)

circle_theta = np.linspace(0, 2 * np.pi, 360)
ax.plot(circle_theta, np.full_like(circle_theta, r_base), color="lightgray", linewidth=2)

for t, r in zip(theta, r_spike):
    ax.plot([t, t], [r_base, r], color="red", linewidth=2)
    ax.plot(t, r, marker="o", color="red")

tick_hours = np.array([1, 4, 7, 10, 13, 16, 19, 22])
tick_theta = 2 * np.pi * (tick_hours - 1) / 24
tick_labels = ["1 AM", "4 AM", "7 AM", "10 AM", "1 PM", "4 PM", "7 PM", "10 PM"]

ax.set_xticks(tick_theta)
ax.set_xticklabels(tick_labels)

ax.set_yticklabels([])

ax.set_title("Clock of Average DAM Price by Hour (Spokes, LZ_WEST, 20242025)", pad=20)
plt.tight_layout()

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from matplotlib.patches import Circle

dfp_all = pd.concat([hourlyprice24.copy(), hourlyprice25.copy()], ignore_index=True)

dfp_all["Hour_of_Day"] = (
    dfp_all["Hour Ending"]
    .astype(str)
    .str.extract(r"(\d{1,2}):")[0]
    .replace("24", "0")
    .astype(int)
    % 24
)

price_col = "Settlement Point Price"
sp_col = "Settlement Point"
sptype_col = "Settlement Point Type" if "Settlement Point Type" in dfp_all.columns else None

if sptype_col:
    dfp_all = dfp_all[dfp_all[sptype_col] == "LZ"]

dfp_all = dfp_all[dfp_all[sp_col] == "LZ_WEST"]
dfp_all[price_col] = pd.to_numeric(dfp_all[price_col], errors="coerce")

q_low = dfp_all[price_col].quantile(0.01)
q_high = dfp_all[price_col].quantile(0.99)
dfp_all[price_col] = dfp_all[price_col].clip(lower=q_low, upper=q_high)

dfp_hourly = dfp_all.groupby("Hour_of_Day")[price_col].mean().reset_index()
dfp_hourly["Price_smooth"] = dfp_hourly[price_col].rolling(window=3, center=True, min_periods=1).mean()

theta = 2 * np.pi * dfp_hourly["Hour_of_Day"] / 24

p = dfp_hourly["Price_smooth"].values
p_norm = (p - p.min()) / (p.max() - p.min() + 1e-9)
p_norm_stretched = p_norm**1.7

r_base = 1.0
r_inner = 0.0
r_outer = r_base + 1.5 * p_norm_stretched

fig = plt.figure(figsize=(8, 8))
ax = fig.add_subplot(111, projection="polar")

ax.set_theta_direction(-1)
ax.set_theta_offset(np.pi / 2)

for t, r in zip(theta, r_outer):
    ax.plot([t, t], [r_inner, r], color="red", linewidth=2)
    ax.plot(t, r, marker="o", color="red")

tick_hours = np.arange(0, 24, 2)
tick_theta = 2 * np.pi * tick_hours / 24
tick_labels = []
for h in tick_hours:
    h12 = h % 12
    h12 = 12 if h12 == 0 else h12
    ampm = "AM" if h < 12 else "PM"
    tick_labels.append(f"{h12} {ampm}")

ax.set_xticks(tick_theta)
ax.set_xticklabels(tick_labels)
ax.set_yticklabels([])

inner_clock = Circle(
    (0.5, 0.5),
    0.20,
    transform=ax.transAxes,
    facecolor="white",
    edgecolor="gray",
    linewidth=1.5,
    zorder=3
)
ax.add_patch(inner_clock)

cx, cy = 0.5, 0.5

hour_3 = 3
angle_3 = np.pi/2 - (hour_3 % 12) * (np.pi/6)
r_long = 0.16
x_long = cx + r_long * np.cos(angle_3)
y_long = cy + r_long * np.sin(angle_3)
ax.plot([cx, x_long], [cy, y_long], transform=ax.transAxes, color="black", linewidth=2, zorder=4)

hour_430 = 4 + 30/60
angle_430 = np.pi/2 - (hour_430 % 12) * (np.pi/6)
r_short = 0.08
x_short = cx + r_short * np.cos(angle_430)
y_short = cy + r_short * np.sin(angle_430)
ax.plot([cx, x_short], [cy, y_short], transform=ax.transAxes, color="black", linewidth=2, zorder=4)

ax.set_title("Average DAM Price by Hour (20242025)", pad=40)
plt.tight_layout()

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm

df_load = pd.concat([hourlyload24.copy(), hourlyload25.copy()], ignore_index=True)

date_load_col = "Delivery Date" if "Delivery Date" in df_load.columns else df_load.columns[0]
hour_load_col = "Hour Ending"   if "Hour Ending" in df_load.columns   else df_load.columns[1]

df_load["date_only"] = pd.to_datetime(df_load[date_load_col], errors="coerce")

h_load = df_load[hour_load_col].astype(str).str.extract(r"(\d{1,2})")[0]
mask = h_load.notna()
df_load = df_load[mask].copy()
h_load = h_load[mask].str.zfill(2)
h_load = h_load.replace("24", "00")

df_load["hour_str"] = h_load
df_load = df_load[df_load["date_only"].notna()].copy()

df_load["key"] = df_load["date_only"].dt.strftime("%Y-%m-%d") + "_" + df_load["hour_str"]

load_numeric = df_load.drop(
    columns=[date_load_col, hour_load_col, "date_only", "hour_str", "key"],
    errors="ignore"
)
load_numeric = load_numeric.apply(pd.to_numeric, errors="coerce")
df_load["system_load"] = load_numeric.select_dtypes(include=["number"]).mean(axis=1)

df_load_small = df_load[["key", "system_load"]].dropna()

df_price = pd.concat([hourlyprice24.copy(), hourlyprice25.copy()], ignore_index=True)

date_price_col = "Delivery Date" if "Delivery Date" in df_price.columns else df_price.columns[0]
hour_price_col = "Hour Ending"   if "Hour Ending" in df_price.columns   else df_price.columns[1]
price_col = "Settlement Point Price"

df_price["date_only"] = pd.to_datetime(df_price[date_price_col], errors="coerce")

h_price = df_price[hour_price_col].astype(str).str.extract(r"(\d{1,2})")[0]
mask_p = h_price.notna()
df_price = df_price[mask_p].copy()
h_price = h_price[mask_p].str.zfill(2)
h_price = h_price.replace("24", "00")

df_price["hour_str"] = h_price
df_price = df_price[df_price["date_only"].notna()].copy()

df_price["key"] = df_price["date_only"].dt.strftime("%Y-%m-%d") + "_" + df_price["hour_str"]

if "Settlement Point Type" in df_price.columns:
    df_price = df_price[df_price["Settlement Point Type"] == "LZ"]

df_price[price_col] = pd.to_numeric(df_price[price_col], errors="coerce")

q_low = df_price[price_col].quantile(0.01)
q_high = df_price[price_col].quantile(0.99)
df_price[price_col] = df_price[price_col].clip(lower=q_low, upper=q_high)

df_price_small = (
    df_price.groupby("key", as_index=False)[price_col]
    .mean()
    .dropna()
)

df_reg = pd.merge(df_load_small, df_price_small, on="key", how="inner").dropna()

X = sm.add_constant(df_reg["system_load"])
y = df_reg[price_col]
model = sm.OLS(y, X).fit()
print(model.summary())

plt.figure(figsize=(8, 5))

plt.scatter(
    df_reg["system_load"],
    df_reg[price_col],
    s=18,
    alpha=0.85,
    edgecolors="black",
    linewidths=0.2
)

x_vals = np.linspace(df_reg["system_load"].min(), df_reg["system_load"].max(), 300)
y_hat = model.params["const"] + model.params["system_load"] * x_vals
plt.plot(x_vals, y_hat, color="red", linewidth=2.5, label="Regression line")

plt.xlabel("System Load (MW)", fontsize=12)
plt.ylabel("DAM Price ($/MWh)", fontsize=12)
plt.title("Hourly DAM Price vs System Load (20242025)\nRegression: Price on Load", fontsize=13)

ax = plt.gca()
ax.spines["top"].set_visible(False)
ax.spines["right"].set_visible(False)
plt.grid(alpha=0.3)
plt.legend()
plt.tight_layout()

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm

# -------- LOAD: system load per hour (no averaging over time) --------
df_load = pd.concat([hourlyload24.copy(), hourlyload25.copy()], ignore_index=True)

load_cols = df_load.columns.tolist()
cols_to_drop = ["Hour Ending"]
for c in ["Delivery Date", "DeliveryDate", "Date"]:
    if c in load_cols:
        cols_to_drop.append(c)

load_numeric = df_load.drop(columns=cols_to_drop, errors="ignore")
load_numeric = load_numeric.apply(pd.to_numeric, errors="coerce")

df_load["system_load"] = load_numeric.select_dtypes(include=["number"]).mean(axis=1)
df_load = df_load.reset_index(drop=True)

# -------- PRICE: LZ_WEST price per hour (no averaging over time) --------
df_price = pd.concat([hourlyprice24.copy(), hourlyprice25.copy()], ignore_index=True)

price_col = "Settlement Point Price"

if "Settlement Point Type" in df_price.columns:
    df_price = df_price[df_price["Settlement Point Type"] == "LZ"]

if "Settlement Point" in df_price.columns:
    df_price = df_price[df_price["Settlement Point"] == "LZ_WEST"]

df_price[price_col] = pd.to_numeric(df_price[price_col], errors="coerce")

q_low = df_price[price_col].quantile(0.01)
q_high = df_price[price_col].quantile(0.99)
df_price[price_col] = df_price[price_col].clip(lower=q_low, upper=q_high)

df_price = df_price.reset_index(drop=True)

# -------- ALIGN BY ROW INDEX (HOURLY RESOLUTION) --------
n = min(len(df_load), len(df_price))

df_reg = pd.DataFrame({
    "system_load": df_load["system_load"].iloc[:n].values,
    price_col: df_price[price_col].iloc[:n].values
}).dropna()

# -------- REGRESSION: PRICE ~ LOAD --------
X = sm.add_constant(df_reg["system_load"])
y = df_reg[price_col]
model = sm.OLS(y, X).fit()
print(model.summary())

# -------- SCATTER + REGRESSION LINE (less transparent dots) --------
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 5))

plt.scatter(
    df_reg["system_load"],
    df_reg[price_col],
    s=12,
    alpha=0.9,
    edgecolors="black",
    linewidths=0.2
)

x_vals = np.linspace(df_reg["system_load"].min(), df_reg["system_load"].max(), 300)
y_hat = model.params["const"] + model.params["system_load"] * x_vals
plt.plot(x_vals, y_hat, color="red", linewidth=2.5, label="Regression line")

plt.xlabel("System Load (MW)", fontsize=12)
plt.ylabel("DAM Price ($/MWh)", fontsize=12)
plt.title("Hourly DAM Price vs System Load (20242025)\nRegression: Price on Load", fontsize=13)

ax = plt.gca()
ax.spines["top"].set_visible(False)
ax.spines["right"].set_visible(False)
plt.grid(alpha=0.3)
plt.legend()
plt.tight_layout()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt


dfp = hourlyprice25.copy()

date_col = dfp.filter(like="Date").columns[0]
hour_col = dfp.filter(like="Hour").columns[0]

dfp["date"] = pd.to_datetime(dfp[date_col], errors="coerce")
dfp["hour"] = (
    dfp[hour_col]
    .astype(str)
    .str.extract(r"(\d{1,2})")[0]
    .replace("24", "00")
)
dfp["hour"] = pd.to_numeric(dfp["hour"], errors="coerce")

price_candidates = [c for c in dfp.columns if "price" in c.lower()]
if price_candidates:
    price_col = price_candidates[0]
    dfp["price"] = pd.to_numeric(dfp[price_col], errors="coerce")
else:
    num_cols = dfp.select_dtypes(include="number").columns
    num_cols = [c for c in num_cols if c not in ["hour"]]
    dfp["price"] = dfp[num_cols].mean(axis=1)

dfp = dfp.dropna(subset=["date", "price"])

daily_arbitrage = (
    dfp.groupby("date")["price"]
       .agg(margin=lambda p: p.max() - p.min())
       .reset_index()
)
daily_arbitrage["month"] = daily_arbitrage["date"].dt.month

month_summary = (
    daily_arbitrage.groupby("month")["margin"]
    .agg(mean="mean", std="std", min="min", max="max")  # no median
    .reset_index()
    .sort_values("mean", ascending=False)
)

month_summary_clean = month_summary.copy()
for col in ["mean", "std", "min", "max"]:
    month_summary_clean[col] = month_summary_clean[col].round(1)

month_summary_clean = month_summary_clean.rename(columns={
    "month": "Month",
    "mean": "Mean",
    "std": "Std Dev",
    "min": "Min",
    "max": "Max"
})

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(7, 2.8))
ax.axis("off")

table = ax.table(
    cellText=month_summary_clean.values,
    colLabels=month_summary_clean.columns,
    loc="center"
)

table.auto_set_font_size(False)
table.set_fontsize(10)
table.scale(1, 1.3)

plt.title("Daily Arbitrage (Buy Low / Sell High) by Month (2025)", pad=20)
plt.tight_layout()

dfp["date"] = pd.to_datetime(dfp[date_col], errors="coerce")

    price_col = price_candidates[0]
    dfp["price"] = pd.to_numeric(dfp[price_col], errors="coerce")
else:

from scipy import stats


dfp = hourlyprice25.copy()

price_candidates = [c for c in dfp.columns if "price" in c.lower()]
if price_candidates:
    price_col = price_candidates[0]
    dfp["price"] = pd.to_numeric(dfp[price_col], errors="coerce")
else:
    num_cols = dfp.select_dtypes(include="number").columns
    dfp["price"] = dfp[num_cols].mean(axis=1)

dfp = dfp.dropna(subset=["date", "price"])

    dfp.groupby("date")["price"]
       .agg(daily_min="min", daily_max="max")
       .reset_index()
)

    may_margins,
    other_margins,
    equal_var=False,
    nan_policy="omit"
)

    p_val_one = p_val_two / 2

print("one-sided p-value:    ", p_val_one)

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from matplotlib.patches import Circle

dfp_all = pd.concat([hourlyprice24.copy(), hourlyprice25.copy()], ignore_index=True)

dfp_all["Hour_of_Day"] = (
    dfp_all["Hour Ending"]
    .astype(str)
    .str.extract(r"(\d{1,2}):")[0]
    .replace("24", "0")
    .astype(int)
    % 24
)

price_col = "Settlement Point Price"
sp_col = "Settlement Point"
sptype_col = "Settlement Point Type" if "Settlement Point Type" in dfp_all.columns else None

if sptype_col:
    dfp_all = dfp_all[dfp_all[sptype_col] == "LZ"]

dfp_all = dfp_all[dfp_all[sp_col] == "LZ_WEST"]
dfp_all[price_col] = pd.to_numeric(dfp_all[price_col], errors="coerce")

q_low = dfp_all[price_col].quantile(0.01)
q_high = dfp_all[price_col].quantile(0.99)
dfp_all[price_col] = dfp_all[price_col].clip(lower=q_low, upper=q_high)

dfp_hourly = dfp_all.groupby("Hour_of_Day")[price_col].mean().reset_index()
dfp_hourly["Price_smooth"] = dfp_hourly[price_col].rolling(window=3, center=True, min_periods=1).mean()

theta = 2 * np.pi * dfp_hourly["Hour_of_Day"] / 24

# raw average prices (for labeling)
p_raw = dfp_hourly[price_col].values
p_min = p_raw.min()
p_max = p_raw.max()

# normalized for spoke length
p = dfp_hourly["Price_smooth"].values
p_norm = (p - p.min()) / (p.max() - p.min() + 1e-9)
p_norm_stretched = p_norm**1.7

r_base = 1.0
r_inner = 0.0
r_outer = r_base + 1.5 * p_norm_stretched

fig = plt.figure(figsize=(8, 8))
ax = fig.add_subplot(111, projection="polar")

ax.set_theta_direction(-1)
ax.set_theta_offset(np.pi / 2)

for t, r in zip(theta, r_outer):
    ax.plot([t, t], [r_inner, r], color="red", linewidth=2)
    ax.plot(t, r, marker="o", color="red")

tick_hours = np.arange(0, 24, 2)
tick_theta = 2 * np.pi * tick_hours / 24
tick_labels = []
for h in tick_hours:
    h12 = h % 12
    h12 = 12 if h12 == 0 else h12
    ampm = "AM" if h < 12 else "PM"
    tick_labels.append(f"{h12} {ampm}")

ax.set_xticks(tick_theta)
ax.set_xticklabels(tick_labels)
ax.set_yticklabels([])

inner_clock = Circle(
    (0.5, 0.5),
    0.20,
    transform=ax.transAxes,
    facecolor="white",
    edgecolor="gray",
    linewidth=1.5,
    zorder=3
)
ax.add_patch(inner_clock)

cx, cy = 0.5, 0.5

hour_3 = 3
angle_3 = np.pi/2 - (hour_3 % 12) * (np.pi/6)
r_long = 0.16
x_long = cx + r_long * np.cos(angle_3)
y_long = cy + r_long * np.sin(angle_3)
ax.plot([cx, x_long], [cy, y_long], transform=ax.transAxes, color="black", linewidth=2, zorder=4)

hour_430 = 4 + 30/60

y_short = cy + r_short * np.sin(angle_430)
ax.plot([cx, x_short], [cy, y_short], transform=ax.transAxes, color="black", linewidth=2, zorder=4)
